TO PICK ME UP.

15:39.569 --> 15:41.511
MY PARENTS TOTALLY
BELIEVE HE´S MY BOYFRIEND.

15:41.511 --> 15:43.943
ZACK, DON´T BLOW THIS.
RELAX.

15:43.943 --> 15:45.515
WE´LL CALL ´EM
ON THE WAY.

15:45.515 --> 15:47.277
COME ON.

15:47.277 --> 15:48.578
ALL RIGHT, FINE,

15:48.578 --> 15:50.620
I´LL MEET YOU
AT THE END OF THE BLOCK.

15:50.620 --> 15:52.252
NOW GO, GET OUT.

15:52.252 --> 15:55.355
HEY, HOW COME YOU NEVER WEAR
THIS TUBE TOP FOR ME?

15:55.355 --> 15:58.428
THAT´S A HEADBAND.

15:58.428 --> 15:59.489
FINE.

15:59.489 --> 16:01.361
THEN PUT
THIS THONG ON.

16:03.093 --> 16:04.234
THAT´S A SHOELACE.

16:04.234 --> 16:06.196
WORK WITH ME.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.169
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:09.169 --> 16:11.201
George: CARMEN,
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

16:11.201 --> 16:12.402
I´LL BE DOWN
IN A MINUTE!

16:12.402 --> 16:14.404
LOOK, HONEY,
THIS CAN´T WAIT.

16:14.404 --> 16:17.277
UH, CAN WE TALK DOWNSTAIRS?
I´M STARVING.

16:17.277 --> 16:19.349
UM, YOU KNOW,
THIS IS KIND OF PRIVATE,

16:19.349 --> 16:21.981
SO SIT DOWN.

16:25.115 --> 16:26.616
LOOK, I KNOW YOU
DON´T LIKE IT

16:26.616 --> 16:28.518
WHEN YOUR MOM AND I
INTERFERE IN YOUR LIFE.

16:28.518 --> 16:30.390
BUT SOMETIMES WE HAVE TO
DO THINGS

16:30.390 --> 16:32.192
THAT ARE
FOR YOUR OWN GOOD.

16:32.192 --> 16:33.993
OH, DADDY, I UNDERSTAND.

16:33.993 --> 16:35.665
I´M GLAD WE HAD THIS TALK.

16:37.327 --> 16:39.169
WELL, LET ME FINISH.

16:40.400 --> 16:43.403
CARMEN, THERE´S NO
EASY WAY TO SAY THIS.

16:43.403 --> 16:46.636
YOUR BOYFRIEND´S
IN THE CLOSET.

16:46.636 --> 16:48.778
OH, MY GOD.

16:50.680 --> 16:54.314
LOOK, I KNOW,
I DON´T LIKE IT EITHER.

16:54.314 --> 16:56.216
BUT JUST BECAUSE
NOAH´S GAY...

16:58.218 --> 17:00.520
OKAY...

17:00.520 --> 17:03.153
IT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU, OKAY?

17:03.153 --> 17:06.526
THIS DOESN´T MEAN THAT YOU´RE
UGLY OR YOU´RE STUPID.

17:06.526 --> 17:09.299
HE WAS JUST USING YOU
TO HIDE SOMETHING

17:09.299 --> 17:11.561
THAT HE DOESN´T
KNOW HOW TO DEAL WITH.

17:13.303 --> 17:15.335
THIS IS SO
DEVASTATING!

17:15.335 --> 17:17.667
AW, HONEY.

17:17.667 --> 17:20.110
I REALLY NEED
SOME TIME ALONE, DAD.

17:20.110 --> 17:21.611
OKAY.

17:21.611 --> 17:24.314
BUT, CARMEN, LOOK, THERE´S
NO WAY YOU COULD HAVE KNOWN.

17:24.314 --> 17:25.645
I MEAN,
THESE THINGS HAPPEN, OKAY?

17:25.645 --> 17:27.447
MRS. GONZALEZ
DOWN THE STREET

17:27.447 --> 17:30.250
STILL DOESN´T KNOW
ABOUT HER HUSBAND, VICTOR.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.482
MR. GONZALEZ IS GAY?

17:32.482 --> 17:34.584
HOW MANY STRAIGHT MEN
DO YOU KNOW

17:34.584 --> 17:37.557
THAT BREED
LABRADOODLES?

17:45.635 --> 17:48.368
HOW´D SHE TAKE IT?
SHE´S PRETTY UPSET.

17:48.368 --> 17:52.102
POOR CARMEN.
SHE MUST FEEL SO BETRAYED.

17:52.102 --> 17:53.643
YEAH, THE WAY YOU
MUST HAVE FELT

17:53.643 --> 17:56.176
WHEN YOU WENT OUT
WITH THAT GUY, BRIAN,

17:56.176 --> 17:57.707
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

17:57.707 --> 17:59.609
BRIAN?

17:59.609 --> 18:01.311
BRIAN WASN´T GAY.

18:03.783 --> 18:06.356
YEAH, HE WAS.

18:06.356 --> 18:08.358
DO YOU REALLY
WANT ME TO TELL YOU

18:08.358 --> 18:11.391
HOW I KNOW BRIAN
WASN´T GAY?

18:14.124 --> 18:15.395
NO.

18:15.395 --> 18:19.229
I´M JUST PLAYING.
HE WAS VERY, VERY GAY.

18:19.229 --> 18:21.531
OKAY,
THAT´S ALL I´M SAYING.

18:21.531 --> 18:23.373
I´M GONNA
BE LATE FOR SCHOOL.

18:23.373 --> 18:25.835
HONEY, ARE YOU OKAY?
DO YOU NEED TO TALK?

18:25.835 --> 18:28.378
TOO SOON, MOM,
TOO SOON.

18:28.378 --> 18:30.280
I´LL CALL HER
ON HER CELL AT LUNCH

18:30.280 --> 18:31.811
TO MAKE SURE
SHE´S ALL RIGHT.

18:34.384 --> 18:36.346
WHAT ABOUT CHAD?

18:36.346 --> 18:38.288
HE WAS GAY.

18:38.288 --> 18:41.551
YES, HE WAS.

18:41.551 --> 18:44.694
EVERYBODY BEFORE YOU
WAS GAY.

18:44.694 --> 18:47.697
THAT´S ALL I´M SAYING.

18:52.302 --> 18:54.704
HEY, MR. AND MRS. LOPEZ,
IS CARMEN READY?

18:54.704 --> 18:56.166
SHE JUST LEFT.

18:56.166 --> 18:57.667
YOU KNOW, NOAH,

18:57.667 --> 18:59.669
I WENT TO SEE "A WALK IN
THE TUSCAN MEADOW" LAST NIGHT.

19:00.840 --> 19:03.713
SAW THE WHOLE THING.

19:03.713 --> 19:05.745
DIDN´T YOU LOVE THE ENDING
WHEN THE CHEESEMAKER

19:05.745 --> 19:07.177
COMES HOME FROM WAR,

19:07.177 --> 19:08.548
BUT HE CAN´T
MAKE CHEESE ANYMORE

19:08.548 --> 19:10.320
BECAUSE HE
LOST HIS ARMS?

19:10.320 --> 19:12.252
BUT THEN HIS SON
SHOWS UP AND SAYS,

19:12.252 --> 19:15.485
"PAPA,
I´LL BE YOUR HANDS."

19:18.588 --> 19:20.660
YEAH, THAT
WAS REALLY MOVING,

19:20.660 --> 19:22.932
BUT I MEANT
THE GAY HORSEPLAY.

19:22.932 --> 19:25.295
WHAT?

19:25.295 --> 19:27.467
MR. LOPEZ SAW YOU...

19:29.469 --> 19:32.472
...BEING VERY FRIENDLY
WITH ANOTHER BOY.

19:32.472 --> 19:35.375
OKAY, WE TALKED
TO CARMEN,

19:35.375 --> 19:36.676
AND IT´S ALL
OUT IN THE OPEN, OKAY?

19:36.676 --> 19:38.508
SO NOBODY HAS TO
SNEAK AROUND ANYMORE.

19:38.508 --> 19:40.210
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, THANK GOD,

19:40.210 --> 19:42.212
´CAUSE I THOUGHT YOU´D
BE MAD AT CARMEN.

19:42.212 --> 19:43.553
